  "body": "The --sort-by option to kubectl top was introduced from v1.15.2 and it accepts only 2 params i.e. cpu and memory.\r\n\r\ne.g. \r\nkubectl top po --all-namespaces --sort-by=cpu\r\nkubectl top po --all-namespaces --sort-by=memory\r\n\r\nThe output is not in a sorted manner.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): v1.15.2\r\n- Cloud provider: GCP/GKE\r\n",
